s Sanders\n  |last2=Lewis\n  |first2=David, trans.\n  |title=Rise and Growth of the Anglican Schism, Translated with an Introduction by David Lewis\n  |location=London\n  |publisher=Burns and Oates\n  |year=1877\n  |url=https://archive.org/stream/riseofschism00sanduoft#page/n5/mode/2up\n  |ref={{sfnref|Sander|1877}}\n}}\n* {{cite book|last=Schofield\n  |first=John\n  |title=The Rise & Fall of Thomas Cromwell: Henry VIII's Most Faithful Servant\n  |year=2011\n  |publisher=The History Press\n  |isbn=978-0-7524-5866-3\n  |ref={{sfnref|Schofield|2011}}\n}}\n* {{cite book |last=Slavin\n  |first=A. J.\n  |title=Politics and profit: A Study of Sir Ralph Sadler 1507-1547\n  |location=Cambridge\n  |publisher=Cambridge University Press\n  |year=2008\n  |isbn=9780521089333\n  |ref={{sfnref|Slavin|2008}}\n}}\n* {{cite book |last=Stoney\n  |first=F. Sadleir\n  |title=A Memoir of the Life and Times of the Right Honourable Sir Ralph Sadleir\n  |year=1877\n  |location=London\n  |publisher=Longmans, Green & Co.\n  |url=https://archive.org/stream/cu31924027961683#page/n5/mode/2up\n  |ref={{sfnref|Stoney|1877}}\n}}\n* {{cite book|last=Strype\n  |first=John\n  |author-link=John Strype\n  |title=Ecclesiastical Memorials\n  |volume=I\n  |issue=II\n  |location=Oxford\n  |publisher=Clarendon Press\n  |year=1822\n  |url=https://archive.org/stream/ecclesiasticalme0102stry#page/n3/mode/2up\n  |ref={{sfnref|Strype I(II)|1822}}\n}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Urban\n  |first=Sylvanus\n  |author-link=Edward Cave\n  |title=The Gentleman's Magazine, and Historical Chronicle, by Sylvanus Urban, Gent.\n  |location=London\n  |publisher=Nichols, Son, and Bentley\n  |date=January\u2013June 1835\n  |volume=III\n  |url=https://archive.org/stream/gentlemansmagaz70unkngoog#page/n6/mode/2up\n  |ref={{sfnref|The Gentleman's Magazine, and Historical Chronicle|January to June 1835}}\n}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{DNB poster|Sadler, Ralph|Ralph Sadler}}\n* [http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1509-1558/member/sadler-ralph-1507-87 SADLER, Ralph (1507-87), of Hackney, Mdx., Standon, Herts. and Lesnes, Kent.] A biography\n* [http://www.metmuseum.org/Collections/search-the-collections/436668 Portrait of a Man (Sir Ralph Sadler?)] A possible portrait\n* {{Find a Grave|12838692}}\n* [http://talltalesfromthetrees.blogspot.com.au/2010/09/sir-ralph-sadleir-1507-1587-and-gossips.html Colin Salter, ''Sir Ralph Sadleir (1507-1587) and the Gossips'']\n* [http://gerryco23.wordpress.com/2013/03/15/sutton-house-home-of-ralph-sadler-late-of-wolf-hall/ Gerry Cordon, ''Sutton House: Home of Ralph Sadler, Late of 'Wolf Hall' '']\n* {{UK National Archives ID}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hon}}\n{{succession box | before=Sir [[Thomas Parry (Comptroller of the Household)|Thomas Parry]] | title=[[Custos Rotulorum of Hertfordshire]] | years=bef. 1562 \u2013 1587 | after=[[John Brograve|Sir John Brograve]]}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Thomas Cromwell]] | title=[[Secretary of State (England)|Secretary of State]] | years=1540\u20131543 |with= [[Thomas Wriothesley, 1st Earl of Southampton|Sir Thomas Wriothesley]]| after=[[Thomas Wriothesley, 1st Earl of Southampton|Sir Thomas Wriothesley]]<br>[[William Paget, 1st Baron Paget|Sir William Paget]]}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Ambrose Cave|Sir Ambrose Cave]] | title=[[Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster]] | years=1568\u20131577 | after=[[Francis Walsingham|Sir Francis Walsingham]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sadler, Ralph}}\n[[Category:Secretaries of State of the Kingdom of England]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the Duchy of Lancaster]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of England to Scotland]]\n[[Category:Court of James V of Scotland]]\n[[Category:English people of the Rough Wooing]]\n[[Category:Scottish Reformation]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of England for Hertfordshire]]\n[[Category:People from Hackney Central]]\n[[Category:1507 births]]\n[[Category:1587 deaths]]\n[[Category:Gentlemen of the Privy C