{"title_page": "Benaraby", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox Australian place\n| type         = town\n| name         = Benaraby\n| state        = qld\n| image        = Benaraby Progress Association Hall.JPG\n| caption      = Benaraby Progress Association Hall, 2017\n| postcode     = 4680\n| area         = 105.8\n| pop          = 594\n| pop_year = {{CensusAU|2006}}\n| pop_footnotes=<ref name=\"ABS\"/>\n| est          =\n| elevation    =\n| pushpin_label_position=left \n| coordinates  = {{coord|23|59|57|S|151|19|04|E|display=inline,title}}\n| maxtemp      =\n| mintemp      =\n| rainfall     =\n| lga          =[[Gladstone Region]]\n|stategov = [[Electoral district of Callide|Callide]]\n|stategov2 = [[Electoral district of Gladstone|Gladstone]]\n| fedgov       =[[Division of Flynn|Flynn]]\n| dist1        =20\n| dir1         =S\n| location1    =[[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]]\n| timezone     =\n| utc          =\n| timezone-dst =\n| utc-dst      =\n}}\n\n'''Benaraby''' is a town and [[Suburbs and localities (Australia)|locality]] in the [[Gladstone Region]], [[Queensland]], Australia.<ref>{{Cite QPN|38878|Benaraby|town|accessdate=24 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite QPN|46589|Benaraby|locality|accessdate=24 June 2017}}</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nBenaraby is 20&nbsp;kilometres south of [[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]] in [[Central Queensland]]. It is on the [[Boyne River (Central Queensland)|Boyne River]] and is the access point to [[Lake Awoonga]], which forms much of the southern boundary of the locality. The Boyne River flows north from the lake through the locality, passing just east of the town, where it is crossed by the [[Bruce Highway]].<ref>{{google maps|url=https://goo.gl/maps/YkKAs3xs34DLV9Hs8 |title=Benaraby, Queensland |accessdate=13 Aug 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nBenaraby Post Office opened around 1912 ([[receiving offices]] known as ''Boyne Bridge'', ''Boyne River'', ''Annandale'' and ''Benaraby'' had been open from 1890) and closed in 1982.<ref name = \"Post Office\">{{Cite web  | last = Premier Postal History  | title = Post Office List  | publisher = Premier Postal Auctions | url = https://www.premierpostal.com/cgi-bin/wsProd.sh/Viewpocdwrapper.p?SortBy=QLD&country= | accessdate = 10 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nOriginally a rural locality, in recent times it has become more of a residential suburb for the workers in [[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]], [[Boyne Island, Queensland|Boyne Island]] and [[Tannum Sands, Queensland|Tannum Sands]].\n\nThe population of Benaraby at the {{CensusAU|2006}} was 594.<ref name=\"ABS\">{{Census 2006 AUS|id=UCL304780|name=Benaraby (Urban Centre/Locality)|accessdate=2008-05-30|quick=on}}</ref>\n\n== Amenities ==\nBenaraby contains 2 petrol stations, a primary school, a community hall, a nursery and three accommodation providers.\n\nBenaraby State School is a public school located in O'Connor Road, Benaraby and caters for students from Prep to Year 6.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://benarabyss.eq.edu.au/Pages/default.aspx|title=Benaraby State School|access-date=17 January 2018}}</ref> It was established in 1886.<ref>{{Cite QldSchool|accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n* [http://queenslandplaces.com.au/gladstone-localities University of Queensland: Queensland Places: Gladstone Localities]\n* [http://benarabyss.eq.edu.au Benaraby State School]\n\n{{Gladstone Region}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Queensland]]\n[[Category:Gladstone Region]]\n[[Category:Localities in Queensland]]\n\n\n{{CentralQueensland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox Australian place\n| type         = town\n| name         = Benaraby\n| state        = qld\n| image        = Benaraby Progress Association Hall.JPG\n| caption      = Benaraby Progress Association Hall, 2017\n| postcode     = 4680\n| area         = 105.8\n| pop          = 594\n| pop_year = {{CensusAU|2006}}\n| pop_footnotes=<ref name=\"ABS\"/>\n| est          =\n| elevation    =\n| pushpin_label_position=left \n| coordinates  = {{coord|23|59|57|S|151|19|04|E|display=inline,title}}\n| maxtemp      =\n| mintemp      =\n| rainfall     =\n| lga          =[[Gladstone Region]]\n|stategov = [[Electoral district of Callide|Callide]]\n|stategov2 = [[Electoral district of Gladstone|Gladstone]]\n| fedgov       =[[Division of Flynn|Flynn]]\n| dist1        =20\n| dir1         =S\n| location1    =[[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]]\n| timezone     =\n| utc          =\n| timezone-dst =\n| utc-dst      =\n}}\n\n'''Benaraby''' is a town and [[Suburbs and localities (Australia)|locality]] in the [[Gladstone Region]], [[Queensland]], Australia.<ref>{{Cite QPN|38878|Benaraby|town|accessdate=24 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite QPN|46589|Benaraby|locality|accessdate=24 June 2017}}</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nBenaraby is 20&nbsp;kilometres south of [[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]] in [[Central Queensland]]. It is on the [[Boyne River (Central Queensland)|Boyne River]] and is the access point to [[Lake Awoonga]], which forms much of the southern boundary of the locality. The Boyne River flows north from the lake through the locality, passing just east of the town, where it is crossed by the [[Bruce Highway]].<ref>{{google maps|url=https://goo.gl/maps/YkKAs3xs34DLV9Hs8 |title=Benaraby, Queensland |accessdate=13 Aug 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nBenaraby Post Office opened around 1912 ([[receiving offices]] known as ''Boyne Bridge'', ''Boyne River'', ''Annandale'' and ''Benaraby'' had been open from 1890) and closed in 1982.<ref name = \"Post Office\">{{Cite web  | last = Premier Postal History  | title = Post Office List  | publisher = Premier Postal Auctions | url = https://www.premierpostal.com/cgi-bin/wsProd.sh/Viewpocdwrapper.p?SortBy=QLD&country= | accessdate = 10 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nOriginally a rural locality, in recent times it has become more of a residential suburb for the workers in [[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]], [[Boyne Island, Queensland|Boyne Island]] and [[Tannum Sands, Queensland|Tannum Sands]].\n\nThe population of Benaraby at the {{CensusAU|2006}} was 594.<ref name=\"ABS\">{{Census 2006 AUS|id=UCL304780|name=Benaraby (Urban Centre/Locality)|accessdate=2008-05-30|quick=on}}</ref>\n\n== Amenities ==\nBenaraby contains 2 petrol stations, a primary school, a community hall, a nursery and three accommodation providers.\n\nBenaraby State School is a public school located in O'Connor Road, Benaraby and caters for students from Prep to Year 6.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://benarabyss.eq.edu.au/Pages/default.aspx|title=Benaraby State School|access-date=17 January 2018}}</ref> It was established in 1886.<ref>{{Cite QldSchool|accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n* [http://queenslandplaces.com.au/gladstone-localities University of Queensland: Queensland Places: Gladstone Localities]\n* [http://benarabyss.eq.edu.au Benaraby State School]\n\n{{Gladstone Region}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Queensland]]\n[[Category:Gladstone Region]]\n[[Category:Localities in Queensland]]\n\n\n{{Queensland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SDZeroBot", "label": "safe", "comment": "Stub sorting: replacing Queensland-geo-stub with CentralQueensland-geo-stub", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benaraby"}
